fulltitle: "Sing With Bobby" - FirstWorks presents Bobby McFerrin
description:
With 20-million albums sold, 10 prestigious Grammy awards, twenty-four years since his celebrated hit "Don't Worry, Be Happy" became an anthem across the globe, FirstWorks presents one of the natural wonders of the musical world, vocalist Bobby McFerrin on May 10, 7:30 pm at The Veterans Memorial Auditorium. Tickets are on sale now for An Evening with Bobby McFerrin; prices start at $22 and are available at vmari.com or 401-421-ARTS (2787) and at first-works.org.

 

McFerrin's solo a cappella concerts have achieved a near-legendary status and have mesmerized audiences from the Far East to the Hollywood Bowl to La Scala.  With remarkable technique and a skill for playfully sparking audience participation, he has carved out a unique place in contemporary vocal performance.  The Los Angeles Times writes, "Bobby McFerrin's greatest gift to his audience may be changing them from spectators into celebrants and transforming a concert hall into a playground, a village center, a joyous space."  With a comedian's sense of timing, an unrestrained zany streak, and an infectious love of every genre of music, McFerrin creates a new kind of concert—not a "performance" but a communal sharing and celebration of music.  For his FirstWorks concert, Bobby invites special guests bassist Jeff Carney and pianist Dan Nagel to the stage.
